dspace-development.title: Symplectic Elements: Searching queues seem frozen

comments.body:
Job scheduling seems to be completely unavailable for the application:

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1443986/160644418-f35e694c-9406-48f5-87e1-79a7b2a911c1.png)

The Synchronization Queues do not seem to be updating:

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1443986/160650512-1920ed7d-83bc-463a-99e0-44544ab9e490.png)

Some of the entries enqueued are from March 2022, hence I suspect that the outdate queue entries might need to be purged:

![image.png](https://images.zenhubusercontent.com/5b5b6aed981c3204c9ed06c8/43d891ba-cfed-4d89-a453-9f01743b3086)
I am now attempting to move one recently-enqueued job to the top priority: ![image.png](https://images.zenhubusercontent.com/5b5b6aed981c3204c9ed06c8/6e703c69-dd34-4496-a2c6-61c05658e892)

The synchronization for these sources seems to be successful, however I do not see any of the respective queue entries being updated:

![image.png](https://images.zenhubusercontent.com/5b5b6aed981c3204c9ed06c8/f44596b5-c748-497d-8a7a-69e98fee5d1e)

Enabling and disabling an individual Data Source was, itself, ineffective. Following this attempt, I am now testing the clearing of a queue, and refilling it: ![image.png](https://images.zenhubusercontent.com/5b5b6aed981c3204c9ed06c8/76313fe3-0e16-4e89-8b73-52e213c3779f)

The activity logs for this do indicate that the Publication records are being updated:

![image.png](https://images.zenhubusercontent.com/5b5b6aed981c3204c9ed06c8/5631928f-cd67-4730-95a0-fd1d6b9a20f1)

@jrgriffiniii Yuan and I are both still experiencing the frozen search. See image:

![image (4)](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/50670293/160706735-a3f5ea83-185b-4582-a80a-6cc3c52d1616.png)

princeton_ansible.title: update vars to use catalog-qa instead of catalog-alma-qa

comments.body: Per @carolyncole and @christinach we will hold off on changes to production.
Related to #2871.
See this [comment](decf558c913b39ffe981632b6ff9cc68111cfc53) for more about the `pg_hba` problem.

The error on the `PostgreSQL | create postgresql database` task is happening because the posgresql role is not creating the correct `pg_hba.conf` entry for this database. The task (`PostgreSQL | ensure access to postgres server for client connections`) uses this formula:
`host  {{ pg_hba_postgresql_database }}      {{ pg_hba_postgresql_user }} {{ ansible_default_ipv4.address }}/32       md5`
and on the staging machine that is currently creating this line:
`host  dbname      pguser ##(ip redacted)##       md5`
which reflects the [default values](https://github.com/pulibrary/princeton_ansible/blob/383f5cb59deb5cb0dc7f899fdd87eba2fa0c6f07/roles/postgresql/defaults/main.yml#L75-L76) in the postgresql role.
Fixing the error reported above required changes to the postgresql role. I've put those changes into a separate PR, so this PR is now blocked until we review and (I hope) merge #2902.
